<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,151,751]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,336,584,608]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named in honour of Dr. Christopher H. Dietrich, University of Illinois, Champaign, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,210,620,644]" name="United States of America" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">USA</collectingCountry>
, who drew our attention to the specimens which constituted the two new genera, 
<taxonomicName box="[1127,1275,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Skandagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1127,1275,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Skandagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1282,1388,620,644]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1282,1388,620,644]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">gen. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,259,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sungallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,259,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sungallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[265,370,656,680]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[265,370,656,680]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">gen. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and in recognition his outstanding contribution to leafhopper systematics.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,151,751]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,692,716]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[585,793,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sungallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis box="[585,793,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sungallia truncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below) but has the subgenital plates triangular rather than truncate as found in the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
